main event: Unidentified objects were observed on radar at Ashiya Air Base, Japan on 15 October 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as luminous, oval-shaped and appeared stationary before moving south and returning north., Multiple radar targets were tracked simultaneously, with speeds estimated between 50-70 mph at 200,000 feet altitude., None of the objects were visually observed despite being tracked on radar for three hours., Four witnesses described the objects as circular or oval, changing color as they moved., The documents concluded the sighting was likely due to radar propagation or interference.
witness description: military personnel at Ashiya Air Base
